<h2 id="03-impacting-humanity">03. Impacting Humanity</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><em>“I immediately think of one of the most famous maps of all time, Maximo Vignelli’s New York City subway map…”</em> referenced Maximo Vignelli’s renowned design for the NYC subway map.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><em>“The word “design” derives from designation…”</em> learn more about the etymology <a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/design" class="note-highlight">here</a>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><em>“I recall John Proctor’s famous line from Arthur Miller’s The Crucible…”</em> watch Daniel Day Lewis as John Proctor deliver this line in a way only he can in Nicholas Hytner’s 1996 film adapation of the Crucible.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

